Soon l'll be able to afford a car

779
01:21:54,583 --> 01:21:57,000
and drive home every night.

780
01:21:57,125 --> 01:22:01,667
Till then, meet me on Friday
and we'll go out.

781
01:24:48,542 --> 01:24:50,583
MOTHER

782
01:24:53,583 --> 01:24:59,125
Psychiatric Helpline.

783
01:25:20,208 --> 01:25:21,583
WHERE & WHEN?

784
01:25:40,292 --> 01:25:45,000
One hour later,
on Boulevard St Martin,

785
01:25:45,125 --> 01:25:47,250
Amelie walks into
a party goods and costume shop.

786
01:25:47,667 --> 01:25:52,083
At the same time,
a man leaves his home on Rue Lecourbe.

787
01:25:54,042 --> 01:25:57,625
20 minutes later,
Amelie is at East Station.

788
01:26:01,958 --> 01:26:05,833
Simultaneously,
the man in red shoes parks outside.

789
01:26:05,958 --> 01:26:09,833
The time is exactly 11.40.

790
01:26:54,958 --> 01:26:57,417
At this precise moment, only Amelie has

791
01:26:57,542 --> 01:27:01,708
the key to the riddle
of the mystery man.

792
01:27:06,375 --> 01:27:08,167
How's it going, Mrs Wells?

793
01:27:08,292 --> 01:27:10,667
Not so bad when it's not raining.

794
01:27:11,250 --> 01:27:14,000
- This is for you.
- Me?

795
01:27:23,500 --> 01:27:27,667
Dear Mrs Wells,
We recently recovered a mailbag

796
01:27:27,792 --> 01:27:30,125
that was lost in a plane crash

797
01:27:30,250 --> 01:27:33,083
on October 12th, 1969
on Mont Blanc.

798
01:27:33,208 --> 01:27:37,500
We are forwarding
the enclosed letter to your address

799
01:27:37,667 --> 01:27:41,333
with our apologies
for the uncustomary delay.

800
01:27:41,792 --> 01:27:45,125
Jacques Grosjean,
Customer Services.

801
01:27:46,042 --> 01:27:50,208
Darling Mado, l'm in exile.
l can't sleep, can't eat...

802
01:27:50,375 --> 01:27:51,667
l think of you endlessly.

803
01:27:51,833 --> 01:27:54,167
l know l've made
the mistake of my life.

804
01:27:54,292 --> 01:27:56,000
l turned down that woman's money.

805
01:27:56,125 --> 01:28:02,542
lf all goes well,
l'll soon be able to afford a house.

806
01:28:02,667 --> 01:28:06,750
l dream of better times ahead

807
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:10,625
when you'll forgive me
and join me here,

808
01:28:10,875 --> 01:28:15,292
one orange-colored day.
Your everloving Adrien.

809
01:28:43,667 --> 01:28:46,542
Another package for you.

810
01:28:55,583 --> 01:28:59,333
You heard about the concierge?

811
01:29:00,500 --> 01:29:01,625
She got a letter.

812
01:29:02,750 --> 01:29:06,500
From her husband. 40 years late!

813
01:29:08,083 --> 01:29:10,750
That's a lot, isn't it?

814
01:29:23,208 --> 01:29:26,625
l'm not big on still life,
Mr Dufayel.

815
01:29:26,875 --> 01:29:29,875
Then work on your lean layer.

816
01:29:30,000 --> 01:29:33,000
Fat over lean. Always!

817
01:29:51,417 --> 01:29:52,333
Mr Dufayel?

818
01:29:52,458 --> 01:29:53,667
Yes?

819
01:29:53,958 --> 01:29:57,417
l heard there'll soon be a new star.

820
01:29:57,667 --> 01:30:00,667
You're into stars now?

821
01:30:00,917 --> 01:30:03,958
l saw it on TV at my ma's, that's why.

822
01:30:04,292 --> 01:30:08,375
l dunno if it's true.

823
01:30:09,833 --> 01:30:14,125
ln America,
they'll take rich people's ashes,

824
01:30:14,250 --> 01:30:17,000
put them in a satellite
and shoot it into space.

825
01:30:17,125 --> 01:30:21,542
lt's going to shine forever.

826
01:30:26,250 --> 01:30:28,292
And Lady Di...

827
01:30:28,458 --> 01:30:30,042
Will they do the same for her?

828
01:30:30,208 --> 01:30:33,417
Lady Di, Lady Di! Give it a rest!

829
01:30:33,625 --> 01:30:36,708
l can't concentrate! Lady Di!

830
01:30:41,833 --> 01:30:43,375
Renoir!

831
01:31:32,500 --> 01:31:35,042
Run, Taly, run!

832
01:31:38,167 --> 01:31:40,667
Run, Taly, run!

833
01:31:47,708 --> 01:31:49,292
You're looking me?

834
01:31:49,458 --> 01:31:52,500
You're looking a man born hard look.

835
01:31:52,667 --> 01:31:58,125
l born in thirteen day
in Friday bad luck day

836
01:32:42,042 --> 01:32:45,250
l don't understand.

837
01:32:51,750 --> 01:32:54,167
Brilliant! You were perfect.

838
01:32:54,292 --> 01:32:55,500
Did it work?

839
01:32:56,000 --> 01:32:57,417
lt's getting there.

840
01:32:57,542 --> 01:33:00,458
Ask me again anytime.
The harm's done.

841
01:33:00,583 --> 01:33:04,583
- Harm?
- Everybody calls me Snow White!

842
01:34:09,583 --> 01:34:12,333
The Two Windmills
from 4 PM.

843
01:34:18,833 --> 01:34:25,042
Could you stand in for me at 4?

844
01:34:25,167 --> 01:34:27,083
Again?

845
01:34:35,000 --> 01:34:37,417
What's eating him?

846
01:34:37,542 --> 01:34:41,292
- l smile too much.
- He'd rather you frowned?

847
01:34:41,417 --> 01:34:43,667
With other men, yes.

848
01:34:46,667 --> 01:34:50,833
Nino is late.
Amelie can only see two explanations.

849
01:34:50,958 --> 01:34:53,833
1: He didn't get the photo.

850
01:34:54,542 --> 01:35:00,125
2: Before he could assemble it

851
01:35:00,250 --> 01:35:01,917
a gang of bank robbers
took him hostage.

852
01:35:02,042 --> 01:35:05,542
The cops gave chase.

853
01:35:05,667 --> 01:35:08,167
They got away but he caused a crash.

854
01:35:10,167 --> 01:35:13,125
When he came to,
he'd lost his memory.

855
01:35:14,167 --> 01:35:16,167
An ex-con picked him up,

856
01:35:16,292 --> 01:35:17,958
mistook him for a fugitive

857
01:35:18,083 --> 01:35:21,208
and shipped him to lstanbul.

858
01:35:21,500 --> 01:35:23,625
He met some Afghan raiders

859
01:35:23,750 --> 01:35:27,000
who took him to steal
some Russian warheads.

860
01:35:31,292 --> 01:35:34,958
But their truck hit a mine
in Tadzhikstan.

861
01:35:35,167 --> 01:35:37,167
He survived, took to the hills

862
01:35:37,292 --> 01:35:39,917
and became a Mujaheddin.

863
01:35:40,208 --> 01:35:41,667
Amelie refuses to get upset
for a guy

864
01:35:41,792 --> 01:35:47,750
who'll eat borscht all his life
in a hat like a tea cozy.

865
01:36:07,167 --> 01:36:09,583
- What can l get you?
- Coffee, please.

866
01:36:10,208 --> 01:36:11,792
Coffee.

867
01:36:34,125 --> 01:36:35,750
Your coffee.

868
01:36:37,083 --> 01:36:38,542
Thanks.

869
01:36:58,000 --> 01:37:04,667
Today's menu

870
01:37:13,375 --> 01:37:18,375
He's understood.
He's going to put down his spoon,

871
01:37:19,833 --> 01:37:23,667
dip his finger in the sugar...

872
01:37:28,583 --> 01:37:32,792
turn around slowly and speak to me.

873
01:37:38,500 --> 01:37:44,375
ls this you?

874
01:37:49,292 --> 01:37:51,792
Yes, it's you.

875
01:37:54,625 --> 01:37:55,708
No.

876
01:38:12,542 --> 01:38:14,917
l clean it for you.

877
01:38:16,125 --> 01:38:19,708
- More coffee?
- No thanks.

878
01:38:40,708 --> 01:38:45,500
So it's this man here,
with his hand up?

879
01:38:45,792 --> 01:38:47,042
Yes.

880
01:38:49,417 --> 01:38:52,292
ls she in love with him?

881
01:38:54,708 --> 01:38:55,750
Yes.

882
01:38:57,792 --> 01:39:02,333
l think it's time
she took a real risk.

883
01:39:02,583 --> 01:39:06,625
She might.
She's devising a stratagem...

884
01:39:06,750 --> 01:39:10,375
She's fond of stratagems.

885
01:39:11,333 --> 01:39:13,958
Mmmm...yes.

886
01:39:14,292 --> 01:39:17,792
ln fact, she's cowardly.

887
01:39:17,917 --> 01:39:22,333
That's why l can't capture her look.

888
01:39:23,500 --> 01:39:28,833
Dufayel's attempts to meddle
are intolerable!

889
01:39:31,125 --> 01:39:35,292
lf Amelie chooses
to live in a dream

890
01:39:35,417 --> 01:39:41,417
and remain
an introverted young woman,

891
01:39:41,542 --> 01:39:46,750
she has an absolute right
to mess up her life!

892
01:40:20,583 --> 01:40:23,292
What are you doing?

893
01:40:24,667 --> 01:40:32,875
Tell me, Lucien. For deliveries,
do you keep keys to all the apartments?

894
01:40:44,333 --> 01:40:48,375
One of your booths is out of order.

895
01:40:50,708 --> 01:40:53,792
lt seems to be jammed.

896
01:40:54,000 --> 01:40:56,375
East Station ticket hall.

897
01:40:59,625 --> 01:41:00,667
Buy a video, get one free?

898
01:41:00,833 --> 01:41:02,417
l don't want to buy.

899
01:41:08,833 --> 01:41:12,458
Samantha?

900
01:41:21,875 --> 01:41:25,292
Can you stand in for me at...

901
01:41:46,583 --> 01:41:51,625
Photo booth, East Station,
Tuesday 5 PM.

902
01:43:03,750 --> 01:43:06,167
Almost done.

903
01:43:10,125 --> 01:43:15,000
The mystery man wasn't a ghost
or a man scared of aging,

904
01:43:15,167 --> 01:43:16,458
but simply the repairman,

905
01:43:16,583 --> 01:43:19,208
a normal guy doing his job.

906
01:44:08,125 --> 01:44:12,625
He keeps spying on me!
lt's making me sick.

907
01:44:12,750 --> 01:44:16,000
4:15 Blatant female conspiracy.

908
01:44:16,625 --> 01:44:22,250
Gosh, you're tense!
Good luck. You'll need it.

909
01:44:30,500 --> 01:44:32,042
Excuse me.
Did you put this in my pocket?

910
01:44:32,167 --> 01:44:35,500
- Yes, but l'm not the one...
- l know. Where is she?

911
01:44:35,667 --> 01:44:41,042
At her father's.
lt bothers me... Can l talk to you?

912
01:44:41,167 --> 01:44:44,000
l get off at six. Can you come back?

913
01:44:44,167 --> 01:44:47,667
Okay.
See you then.

914
01:44:48,208 --> 01:44:51,042
4.08: Docking scheduled.

915
01:45:22,333 --> 01:45:27,208
A blond guy in a camel coat.
Absent-minded, too.

916
01:45:27,458 --> 01:45:29,167
How come?

917
01:45:29,667 --> 01:45:32,417
He came back 3 times the same day.

918
01:45:33,458 --> 01:45:36,708
1.12: Camel coat.

919
01:45:36,833 --> 01:45:38,958
2.50: Camel coat.

920
01:45:39,250 --> 01:45:42,292
- 4.17...
- Stop it!

921
01:45:42,458 --> 01:45:44,667
My rash has come back!

922
01:45:44,792 --> 01:45:48,167
Look, Suzanne! My rash is back.

923
01:45:48,333 --> 01:45:50,083
He's driving me nuts!

924
01:45:50,208 --> 01:45:52,333
Lay off!

925
01:45:52,583 --> 01:45:55,167
Her conscience is at fault.

926
01:45:55,333 --> 01:45:58,500
l've had it! l'm going home.

927
01:45:58,833 --> 01:46:01,833
Psychos are the last straw!

928
01:46:02,000 --> 01:46:03,917
Georgette!

929
01:46:05,958 --> 01:46:09,667
Stop smothering them!
Women need air.

930
01:46:09,833 --> 01:46:12,792
You give them air, they blow you off.

931
01:46:12,958 --> 01:46:14,625
Fresh air's healthy.

932
01:46:14,750 --> 01:46:17,583
Cram it, failure!

933
01:46:17,708 --> 01:46:21,500
Failed writer, failed life...

934
01:46:21,667 --> 01:46:23,375
l love the word ''fail''.

935
01:46:23,500 --> 01:46:25,333
Failure is human destiny.

936
01:46:25,500 --> 01:46:27,292
lt's gasbag time!

937
01:46:27,417 --> 01:46:31,750
Failure teaches us
that life is but a draft,

938
01:46:31,875 --> 01:46:35,833
a long rehearsal
for a show that will never play.

939
01:46:36,083 --> 01:46:39,125
l bet he stole that!

940
01:46:39,458 --> 01:46:41,000
l do have some original ideas,

941
01:46:41,333 --> 01:46:43,208
but people always steal them.

942
01:46:44,500 --> 01:46:46,375
Same as your women.

943
01:46:47,000 --> 01:46:48,458
Meaning?

944
01:46:49,125 --> 01:46:51,875
You'd better get used to it.

945
01:46:52,167 --> 01:46:55,208
Speak for yourself, you...

946
01:46:55,333 --> 01:47:00,000
- What's going on?
- Nothing much.

947
01:47:00,167 --> 01:47:03,917
Georgette went out. Joseph got mad.

948
01:47:04,042 --> 01:47:05,375
''Went out?''

949
01:47:05,500 --> 01:47:08,958
Like Gina. You know who Gina's with?

950
01:47:09,125 --> 01:47:12,333
The guy with the plastic bag!

951
01:47:12,625 --> 01:47:14,792
l saw their little game.

952
01:47:15,000 --> 01:47:16,292
The note in the coat pocket,

953
01:47:16,417 --> 01:47:17,708
4.20.

954
01:47:17,833 --> 01:47:22,708
Back he comes, and hey presto!
Out they go.

955
01:47:26,708 --> 01:47:29,750
l'm worried for Amelie
because l like you.

956
01:47:29,875 --> 01:47:30,750
What do you mean?

957
01:47:31,292 --> 01:47:34,958
By and large,
the men l like are mentally unsound.

958
01:47:35,292 --> 01:47:38,333
- l'd like to know more about you.
- Ask me.

959
01:47:38,500 --> 01:47:43,000
One swallow doesn't make?

960
01:47:43,750 --> 01:47:45,250
A swallow?

961
01:47:46,458 --> 01:47:47,958
A summer.

962
01:47:48,125 --> 01:47:49,333
Practice makes...

963
01:47:49,500 --> 01:47:50,875
Perfect.

964
01:47:51,000 --> 01:47:52,708
- Curiosity...
- Killed the cat.

965
01:47:52,833 --> 01:47:54,000
- Haste...
- Makes waste.

966
01:47:54,167 --> 01:47:55,625
- Rolling stone...
- Gathers no moss.

967
01:47:55,792 --> 01:47:58,000
- lt's a sin...
- To steal a pin.

968
01:47:58,167 --> 01:48:01,958
- Absence makes?
- The heart grow fonder.

969
01:48:02,083 --> 01:48:04,125
- Not bad.
- You collect them?

970
01:48:04,250 --> 01:48:08,917
At home, we say a man
who knows proverbs can't be all bad.

971
01:48:12,750 --> 01:48:15,125
Pretty girl from the 5th floor,
listen to this!

972
01:48:15,250 --> 01:48:19,667
- You believe in miracles?
- Not today.

973
01:48:20,583 --> 01:48:22,292
You're in for a surprise.

974
01:48:22,417 --> 01:48:25,333
What if l told you that
a team of climbers on Mont Blanc

975
01:48:25,458 --> 01:48:30,750
had found hard proof that
my husband loved me?

976
01:49:07,875 --> 01:49:10,167
Lucien, l need some yeast.

977
01:49:10,333 --> 01:49:14,208
For Miss Amelie?
She's baking her famous plumcake?

978
01:49:14,333 --> 01:49:17,458
Lucien, go to get some yeast.

979
01:50:11,250 --> 01:50:15,000
Amelie! Amelie!

980
01:50:21,292 --> 01:50:22,958
Amelie!

981
01:50:43,625 --> 01:50:47,000
l'll be back

982
01:51:16,333 --> 01:51:19,458
Go into the bedroom, Miss Poulain.

983
01:51:35,333 --> 01:51:39,583
So, little Amelie.

984
01:51:40,000 --> 01:51:42,625
Your bones aren't made of glass.

985
01:51:42,750 --> 01:51:45,958
You can take life's knocks.

986
01:51:46,167 --> 01:51:49,833
lf you let this chance go by,

987
01:51:50,000 --> 01:51:54,875
eventually, your heart will become

988
01:51:55,000 --> 01:52:00,333
as dry and brittle as my skeleton.

989
01:52:00,667 --> 01:52:09,458
So... Go get him, for Pete's sake!

990
01:54:57,167 --> 01:55:02,208
''Without you, today's emotions
would be the scurf of yesterday's''

991
01:55:58,875 --> 01:56:00,875
lnternational airport.

992
01:56:01,125 --> 01:56:04,000
September 28th, 1997.
lt is exactly 11 AM.

993
01:56:04,167 --> 01:56:05,625
At the funfair,
near the Ghost Train,

994
01:56:05,792 --> 01:56:09,958
the marshmallow twister is twisting,

995
01:56:10,083 --> 01:56:13,958
while in Villette Park,

996
01:56:14,083 --> 01:56:15,542
Felix Lerbier learns

997
01:56:15,667 --> 01:56:20,500
there are more links in
his brain than atoms in the universe.

998
01:56:21,083 --> 01:56:25,792
At the Sacre Coeur, the Carmelites
are practicing their backhand.

